  "notes": "Neapolitan. Southern Italo-Romance of Campania and broader S. mainland Italy. ~5.7 million speakers. Key features: (1) Metaphony (vowel harmony triggered by final vowel). (2) Unstressed vowels → [ə]. (3) Rich gemination. (4) Retroflex -DD- [ɖː] in some areas. Literary tradition from 16th c. (Ledgeway 2009, De Blasi & Imperatore 2000).",
